dashboardItems.text:
*NOTES ON INDICATORS*

*ANC0001 Clients with a ANC first contact in the first trimester* is based on registrations within the reporting period, including open and closed records.

*ANC0101 Clients with ultrasound scan before 24wk* is based on all records where the client is assumed to have passed gestational age of 24 weeks during the reporting period, including open and closed records.

All other indicators exclusively measure closed ANC records in both numerator and denominator. Periodicity is assigned by the period in which the ANC closure event occurs, not the date of registration. It is therefore very important that open ANC records over 42 weeks gestational age are followed up and closed as necessary.

Indicator definitions and codes are derived from the core indicators presented in the Digital Adaptation Kit for Antenatal Care, Annex C (Indicators Table) found here: https://www.who.int/publications/i/item/9789240020306

dataElements.description: A urine test is required at the first contact, last contact in 2nd trimester, and 2nd contact in 3rd trimester OR anytime the woman reports pain during urination (dysuria). A dipstick test is required if the woman has a repeat high BP reading (140/90 or higher). Otherwise, a urine test is optional. The urine test checks for bacterial or other infections that can lead to adverse outcomes for the neonate. The urine dipstick test can check for proteins in the urine, which can be a sign of pre-eclampsia.
